						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is highly damaged, and also fragmentary. It mentions the name of the division Vallanāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jayaṅgoṇḍa Pāṉ[ḍiyapuram*]. One of the fragmentary inscriptions mentions the king, Tribhuvaṇachakravartigal Śri Vikramapāṇḍyadēvar Jayaṅgoṇḍa Pāṇḍipurattu Śri Kulaśēkharadēvar, respectively. Another one refers to a land donation to burn lamps before the deity etc.</p>						

						</summary>
